title: X-Ray
description: X-rays are a form of electromagnetic radiation used to create images of the inside of the body. This technology is particularly effective for visualizing bones and detecting fractures.

title: Ultrasonography
description: Ultrasonography, or ultrasound, uses high-frequency sound waves to create real-time images of the body's internal organs and tissues. It is commonly used in prenatal care to monitor fetal development.

title: Blood Test
description: Blood tests are essential diagnostic tools that analyze a sample of blood to assess various health parameters. They can measure levels of glucose, cholesterol, electrolytes, and other substances.
